<h2 id=3D"search-the-index">Search the index</h2>
<p>Now that you have an index, you can search it.</p>
<ol class=3D"taskList">
<li class=3D"task-list-item" id=3D"taskIndex30"><p><label class=3D"checkbox=
"><input type=3D"checkbox" aria-labelledby=3D"taskIndex30"><span></span></l=
abel>Return to the <strong>Overview</strong> page for your Azure AI Search =
resource, and on the toolbar, select <strong>Search explorer</strong>.</p><=
/li>
<li class=3D"task-list-item" id=3D"taskIndex31"><p><label class=3D"checkbox=
"><input type=3D"checkbox" aria-labelledby=3D"taskIndex31"><span></span></l=
abel>In Search explorer, in the <strong>Query string</strong> box, enter <c=
ode class=3D"prettyprint prettyprinted" tabindex=3D"0" style=3D""><span cla=
ss=3D"pun">*</span></code> (a single asterisk), and then select <strong>Sea=
rch</strong>.</p>
<p>This query retrieves all documents in the index in JSON format. Examine =
the results and note the fields for each document, which contain document c=
ontent, metadata, and enriched data extracted by the cognitive skills you s=
elected.</p></li>
<li class=3D"task-list-item" id=3D"taskIndex32"><p><label class=3D"checkbox=
"><input type=3D"checkbox" aria-labelledby=3D"taskIndex32"><span></span></l=
abel>In the <strong>View</strong> menu, select <strong>JSON view</strong> a=
