se data analysis solution.</p>
<h3 id=3D"view-file-projections">View file projections</h3>
<p>The <em>file</em> projections defined in the skillset create JPEG files =
for each image that was extracted from the documents during the indexing pr=
ocess.</p>
<ol class=3D"taskList">
<li class=3D"task-list-item" id=3D"taskIndex60"><label class=3D"checkbox"><=
input type=3D"checkbox" aria-labelledby=3D"taskIndex60"><span></span></labe=
l>In the <em>Storage browser</em> interface in the Azure portal, select the=
 <strong>margies-skillset-image-projection</strong> blob container. This co=
ntainer contains a folder for each document that contained images.</li>
<li class=3D"task-list-item" id=3D"taskIndex61"><label class=3D"checkbox"><=
input type=3D"checkbox" aria-labelledby=3D"taskIndex61"><span></span></labe=
l>Open any of the folders and view its contents - each folder contains at l=
east one *.jpg file.</li>
<li class=3D"task-list-item" id=3D"taskIndex62"><label class=3D"checkbox"><=
input type=3D"checkbox" aria-labelledby=3D"taskIndex62"><span></span></labe=
l>Open any of the image files, and download and view it to see the image.</=
li>
</ol>
<p>The ability to generate <em>file</em> projections like this makes indexi=
ng an efficient way to extract embedded images from a large volume of docum=
ents.</p>
<h3 id=3D"view-table-projections">View table projections</h3>
<p>The <em>table</em> projections defined in the skillset form a relational=
 schema of enriched data.</p>
<ol class=3D"taskList">
<li class=3D"task-list-item" id=3D"taskIndex63"><label class=3D"checkbox"><=
input type=3D"checkbox" aria-labelledby=3D"taskIndex63"><span></span></labe=
l>In the <em>Storage browser</em> interface in the Azure portal, expand <st=
rong>Tables</strong>.</li>
<li class=3D"task-list-item" id=3D"taskIndex64"><label class=3D"checkbox"><=
input type=3D"checkbox" aria-labelledby=3D"taskIndex64"><span></span></labe=
l>Select the <strong>margiesSkillsetDocument</strong> table to view data. T=
his table contains a row for each document that was indexed:</li>
<li class=3D"task-list-item" id=3D"taskIndex65"><label class=3D"checkbox"><=
input type=3D"checkbox" aria-labelledby=3D"taskIndex65"><span></span></labe=
l>View the <strong>margiesSkillsetKeyPhrases</strong> table, which contains=
 a row for each key phrase extracted from the documents.</li>
</ol>
<p>The ability to create <em>table</em> projections enables you to build an=
alytical and reporting solutions that query a relational schema. The automa=
tically generated key columns can be used to join the tables in queries - f=
or example to return all of the key phrases extracted from a specific docum=
ent.</p>
